      "question_id": "q3",
      "answer": "Yes, add E2E tests to the CI pipeline. The current CI already runs backend pytest, frontend vitest, and a build step in a single job on ubuntu-latest. Adding Playwright requires: (1) npx playwright install --with-deps chromium (~15-20s), (2) starting the Vite dev server via Playwright's webServer config (automatic). With mocked APIs, the Python backend is NOT needed in CI. Total added CI time: ~1-2 minutes for Chromium-only. The playwright.config.ts webServer block handles starting/stopping the dev server automatically.",
