        ".github/workflows/ci.yml:1-48 (current CI: pytest, vitest, build on ubuntu-latest)",
        ".github/workflows/ci.yml:30-32 (Node 22 already set up)",
        ".github/workflows/ci.yml:35-36 (pnpm already installed)"
      ],
      "uncertainty": "Exact CI time impact. Playwright browser install can be cached with actions/cache but adds config complexity."
    },
    {
      "question_id": "q4",
      "answer": "Chromium only for the initial scope. This is the standard Playwright default for speed. The app uses standard React with no browser-specific APIs (no WebRTC, no canvas-heavy rendering). Cross-browser issues are unlikely for a data-driven SPA. Firefox and WebKit can be added later with a one-line config change in playwright.config.ts projects array. Each additional browser adds ~30-60s of install + run time to CI.",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "evidence": [
        "frontend/package.json:14-19 (standard React + React Router + TanStack Query + Recharts)",
        "frontend/src/app/App.tsx:1-63 (standard inline styles, no browser-specific CSS)"
      ],
      "uncertainty": "Recharts (SVG-based charting library) could have minor cross-browser rendering differences, but these wouldn't affect happy-path functional tests."
    },
    {
      "question_id": "q5",
      "answer": "Use localStorage injection for most tests, with one dedicated test verifying the header input flow. The localStorage format is simple JSON under key 'bayes-session': {\"accountId\": \"...\", \"agentId\": \"...\"}. Injection via page.addInitScript() before navigation is the standard Playwright pattern. The header inputs are plain <input> elements with placeholder text 'Account ID' and 'Agent ID (optional)' — no data-testid attributes, but placeholders work as Playwright locators via page.getByPlaceholder().",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "evidence": [
        "frontend/src/features/session/context.tsx:4 (STORAGE_KEY = 'bayes-session')",
        "frontend/src/features/session/context.tsx:6-17 (loadSession reads/parses localStorage)",
        "frontend/src/features/session/context.tsx:19-21 (saveSession writes JSON to localStorage)",
        "frontend/src/app/App.tsx:25-36 (header inputs with placeholder text, no data-testid)"
      ],
      "uncertainty": "None significant. localStorage injection is a well-established Playwright pattern."
    },
    {
      "question_id": "q6",
      "answer": "Focus on core trading-relevant sections for the initial happy path. Recommended scope per view: (1) MarketList: page loads with market cards, search filters results, sort changes order, click navigates to detail — ~3-4 tests. (2) MarketDetail: header/title loads, probability bar displays outcomes, trading panel interaction works — ~4-5 tests. (3) Trade execution: select outcome, enter size, submit order, verify receipt/confirmation — ~2-3 tests. (4) Portfolio: loads with account configured, shows risk metrics (limit, available, utilization, health), shows positions table — ~3-4 tests. Total: ~12-16 tests across 4 spec files. Sections like BayesNetGraph, JunctionTreePanel, and detailed analytics charts can be deferred.",
